AU  - Liu, JK
AU  - Zhuang, MZ
AU  - Li, SM
AU  - Zhao, SM
AU  - Huang, B
TI  - System Dynamic Analysis of Disposal Policy of Construction and Demolition Waste in Urban Village
T2  - EKOLOJI
AB  - Recent years have witnessed great changes in urban villages, urban-rural continuum, etc. with the development of China's economy and the deepening of urbanization construction. The old village houses have been replaced by new houses, and the transformation of urban villages is particularly obvious. Due to the weak environmental awareness of the villagers, the construction of self-built houses in rural areas easily produces a large amount of construction and demolition waste (C&DW), and at the same time, environmental pollution is deteriorating due to illegal dumping of C&DW. The introduction of disposal policy always concerns C&DW. Therefore, this paper establishes a system dynamics model and simulates the relevant countermeasures with Guangzhou Xiancun as an example. The results of policy simulation show that: (1) Administrative penalty and fund subsidy policies can effectively reduce illegal waste dumping, but the penalty and subsidy policies do not always follow the rule of "bigger is better". Simulation analysis reveals that penalty amount should be in the range of (300,350) CNY / t, and subsidy should be in the range of (20, 30) CNY / t. (2) The unit transportation cost for comprehensive disposal and the unit transportation cost for recycling will affect the amount of comprehensive disposal and recycling of C&DW, but the impact is limited. (3) The impact of administrative penalties, fund subsidies and transportation cost factors on the amount of C&DW generated is not long-term. The conclusions of the study will help strengthen the government's management of rural C&DW recycling and provide reference for its policy formulation.
