TI  - STABILITY ANALYSIS OF CRUSHED STONE BASED ON ECOLOGICAL ENVIRONMENT RECYCLED AGGREGATE SUBGRADE
T2  - FRESENIUS ENVIRONMENTAL BULLETIN
AB  - With the rapid development of the construction industry, the construction waste generated by the construction industry has also increased unprecedentedly, which has a certain impact on the environment and a certain hazard to the society. The technology of using waste concrete as recycled aggregate after crushing, removing impurities, grading, and using recycled aggregate to prepare recycled concrete can not only solve the environmental pollution caused by waste concrete, but also save natural aggregate resources and bring significant social benefits, economic benefits, and ecological environmental benefits. This paper experimentally determines the main mechanical properties of recycled aggregate lime-ash gravel such as the maximum dry density, optimal water content, unconfined compressive strength, indirect tensile strength and indoor compressive resilience modulus, and compare with the parameters of natural aggregate crushed stone. The experimental results show that the mechanical stability of recycled aggregate lime-ash crushed stone is stronger than the parameter value of natural aggregate crushed stone. The main mechanical properties of lime-ash gravel meet the requirements of road engineering for bearing base and it is feasible to use recycled aggregate to replace natural aggregate for road lime-ash crushed stone base,
